description: Proper Japanese Title: 決戦！あきらめない戦士たちの奇跡の力 (Kessen! Akiramenai Senshi-tachi no Kiseki no Pawā)
name: Showdown! The Unyielding Warriors’ Miraculous Super Power

description: Proper Japanese Title: 新たなＨＯＰＥ！！を胸に さらばトランクス (Arata na Kibō!! O Mune ni Saraba Torankusu)
name: Fill Your Heart with New Hope!! Farewell, Trunks

description: S.H.I.E.L.D. and Ghost Rider find themselves unlikely allies when the lives of all of Los Angeles hang in the balance.
name: The Laws of Inferno Dynamics

description: Someone stumbles upon a brand new society, and this society is unlike anything seen before.
name: Swear

description: Proper Japanese Title: いでよ神龍！叶える願いは誰のもの！？ (Ide yo Shenron! Kanaeru Negai wa Dare no Mono!?)
name: Come Forth, Shenlong! Whose Wish Shall Be Granted?!

description: The cadets come together for graduation day, but Spyro will need to overcome his bad attitude and big ego to join his friends as a Skylander.
name: Skylanders Unite!

description: Jet-Vac uses a potential plumbing disaster to teach Spyro about the "Skylander way", but they clash over Jet-Vac's strict rules and planning.
name: My Way or the Sky Way

deck: kara trying to save mon el live
description: As Eliza comes to National City for Thanksgiving, Kara turns to Lena for help when Cadmus unleashes a virus that instantly kills aliens, then is asked by Barry Allen and Cisco Ramon for help with an alien invasion on their Earth.
name: Medusa

description: Mario and Gordon face off before the wedding, Selina meets an unexpected face and Barbara comes to Nygma with information about Isabella.
name: Beware the Green-Eyed Monster

description: When the Skylanders struggle to work as a team, sensei King Pen shows them how to build a new teammate that combines their talents.
name: Missing Links

description: Stealth Elf is chosen to give a speech to the entire academy, but first she has to figure out why everyone is suddenly terrified of sheep.
name: Dream Girls

description: The young Skylanders are assigned to spend a day as guards at Cloudcracker Prison, and the inmates try to trick the heroes into letting them escape.
name: The Hole Truth

description: Barry asks Green Arrow for help when aliens attack Central City, but when they realize that won't be enough, they track down the Legends of Tomorrow so they can bring Supergirl in on the battle.
name: Invasion!

deck: Oliver wakes up to a life in which his parents are alive
description: Oliver wakes up to a life in which his parents are alive and he is about to marry Laurel; Felicity faces a new threat with the help of The Flash and Supergirl.
name: Invasion!

description: The Legends work with The Flash, Supergirl and Green Arrow to kill the invaders; while working out how to defeat the Dominators, Stein gets distracted by the aberration he created in 1987.
name: Invasion!

description:
Japanese title: Yami wo Kiru (闇を斬る).

Tatsumi leaves his village in pursuit of wealth and success in the Imperial Capital. He attempts to join the army, however it isn’t as easy as it seems. When all of the sudden, a large breasted woman shows up at the local bar and offers to help him get recruited.
name: Kill the Darkness

description:
Japanese title: Kenryoku wo Kiru (権力を斬る)

Tatsumi is taken by the Night Raid. They realized his potential as an assassin and asks him to join, but Tatsumi is conflicted. Though after learning more about each of Night Raid’s team members, he learns of their objectives to defeat evil and corruption and eventually decides to join.
name: Kill the Authority

description:
Japanese title: Wadakamari wo Kiru (蟠（ワダカマリ）を斬る)

The Night Raid’s hideout is invaded by intruders! The assassin clan was able to drive out the enemy without a problem. Tatsumi experiences the true intensity of the Night Raid for the first time and he is thrilled.
name: Kill Your Cares

description:
Japanese title: Teigu Tsukai wo Kiru (帝具使いを斬る)

The target this time is the capital’s rumored phantom serial killer known only as “Zank the Executioner.” Just like the Night Raid, he is an Imperial Arms user as well.
name: Kill the Imperial Arm Users

description:
Japanese title: Yumemonogatari wo Kiru (夢物語を斬る)

Sheele, who has no particular role in the hideout is assigned as Tatsumi’s trainer. She explains how and why she chose assassinating as her career. Tatsumi, who still doesn’t have an Imperial Arm of his own, tests out the Imperial Arm taken from Zank.
name: Kill the Dream

description:
Japanese title: Zettai Seigi wo Kiru (絶対正義を斬る)

Night Raid is tasked with the eradication of a drug trafficking organization within the Imperial City. Tatsumi and Leone head towards the red light district. The two learn of the horrific details of the organization and their rage is apparent. Meanwhile, Sheele and Mine go after the Tybil, former leader of the organization when they suddenly feel an alarming presence.
name: Kill the Absolute Justice

description:
Japanese title: Sanbiki wo Kiru - Zenpen - (三匹を斬る - 前編 -)

General Esdeath arrives at the capital and is brought to the Emperor to discuss annihilating Night Raid. The Emperor wants to reward her for her services but her request is somewhat surprising.
name: Kill the Three, Part 1

description:
Japanese title: Sanbiki wo Kill - Kouhen - (三匹を斬る - 後編 -)

Tatsumi and Bulat stand before the Three. Among them is Bulat’s former leader, Liver. The battle quickly turns into a one-on-one combat between Bulat versus Liver and Tatsumi versus Nyau.
name: Kill the Three, Part 2

description:
Japanese title: Sentoukyou wo Kiru (戦闘狂を斬る)

Tatsumi inherits Bulat’s Imperial Arms Incrusio after defeating the Three and vows to become even stronger. Mine’s attitude towards Tatsumi seems to show a change after seeing his dedication during training... Meanwhile, General Esdeath receives news of the Three being defeated and in order to reinforce the army’s strength she organizes a special police force of Imperial Arms users known only as the Jeagars.
name: Kill the Battle Fanatic

description:
Japanese title: Yuuwaku wo Kiru (誘惑を斬る)

Esdeath has taken Tatsumi after winning the combat tournament. And the reason being... love at first sight?! That being said Tatsumi has not only been forced to become Esdeath’s lover but also an auxiliary member of the Jaegers. Tatsumi and Esdeath observe as the Jaegers raid the bandits’ hideout; he witnesses how powerful the Jaegers truly are. All the while Tatsumi tries to find an opportunity to escape and return to the Night Raid’s hideout...
name: Kill the Temptation

description:
Japanese title: Mad Scientist wo Kiru (マッドサイエンティストを斬る)

Dr. Stylish discovered Night Raid’s hideout as he followed Tatsumi. A battle quickly commenced between Night Raid and Dr. Stylish’s fortified army who struck with a surprise attack. Tatsumi and Mine are enraged as they see Kakusan equipped with Sheele’s Imperial Arms Extase. A fierce battle continues within the hideout when suddenly something came down from the Sky...
name: Kill the Mad Scientist

description:
Japanese title: Shiniri wo Kiru (新入りを斬る)

After dealing with Dr. Stylish’s attack Night Raid leaves their base and hides in the mountains. After welcoming the newly joined member, Night Raid experienced a brief moment of peace, even amid training. Mine, who has been teased relentlessly Chelsea, the newcomer, tells Tatsumi and Lubbok that she wants revenge.
name: Kill the Newcomers

description:
Japanese title: Jamamono wo Kiru (邪魔者を斬る)

A new species of Danger Beasts have emerged and has been terrorizing the vicinity of the capital. Minister Onest has ordered Esdeath to seize and defeat them. Esdeath leads the Jaegers to go to deal with them. But something suspicious in the shadow is keeping an eye on their actions. Meanwhile, after Night Raid settles into their new hideout, they’re also on the move to deal with the new Danger Beasts.
name: Kill the Nuisances
Goku vs Arale! A Ridiculous Battle Will End the Earth?!

description: A deeper look at the Sanctuary and the world of the Saviors; members of Alexandria look for supplies.
name: Sing Me a Song

description: His plans left in ruins, Ghetsis makes one last attempt to bring Unova under his icy grasp. A hero arrives, intending to stop him.
name: The King Returns

description: Stealth Elf finds trouble when she gets stuck inside Kaos's mind, and she has to convince the others that she's trapped so they can help her escape.
name: Space Invaders

deck: The Enterprise crew are trapped on a planet of people with psionic powers
description: A handful of humans with psionic powers and a society modeled on Plato's writings keep the Enterprise crew hostage because they need the medical services of Dr. McCoy.
name: Plato's Stepchildren

deck: Barry heads for Earth-3 to get advice from Jay Garrick
description: Barry heads for Earth-3 to get advice from Jay Garrick on how to stop Savitar; Wally tells Barry he's been training with H.R.; old wounds are reopened as Cisco faces Christmas without Dante.
name: The Present

deck: Oliver realizes Prometheus is planning to make a deadly move on all of Team Arrow
description: After the attack on Curtis, Oliver realizes Prometheus is planning to make a deadly move on all of Team Arrow; Felicity and Malone find a clue that ties Prometheus to Oliver's past.
name: What We Leave Behind

description: The Legends track a Time Aberration to 1927 Chicago and realize they've been set up by Eobard Thawne, Damien Dahrk and the newest member of the Legion of Doom - Malcolm Merlyn.
name: The Chicago Way

description: Before they can enjoy Halloween, the Rangers are summoned to the Intergalactic Court by Scumlaw for their crimes against the monsters they have destroyed.
name: Trick or Trial

description: Scientist. Entrepreneur. Visionary. Take a closer look at the man whose acts have redefined the Kalos region: Lysandre.
name: The Beauty Eternal

description: Negan's unwelcome visit to Alexandria continues as other members scavenge for supplies; things quickly spin out of control.
name: Hearts Still Beating
The World is Not in Here

description: Champa contacts Beerus and challenges him to a game of baseball, as a way of "cultivating the friendship" between Universes 6 and 7 and both teams are having trouble of how to play the game properly.
name: Champa's Challenge! This Time We Fight With Baseball!

name: City of the Dancing Mask

description: The trial begins, and the prosecution is helmed by the daughter of a fallen foe, out for revenge.
name: Reunion and Turnabout - 2nd Trial

description: After the first session of the trial, the investigation continues, and a few suspects start to crop up.
name: Reunion and Turnabout - 3rd Trial

description: The trial reaches its climax, and the culprit is well and truly unmasked.
name: Reunion and Turnabout - Last Trial

description: A new murder, a new case. This time, the crime scene is a circus.
name: Turnabout Big Top - 1st Trial

description: The trial for the murder of the circus ringmaster begins, and a shocking fact is revealed to the court.
name: Turnabout Big Top - 2nd Trial

description: Eruptor goes to anger management when his temper puts missions at risk, but he'll need to tap back into his rage to get the Skylanders out of trouble.
name: Anger Mismanagement

description: Detective Looker's assistants Emma and Mimi have been helping him out in Lumiose City, until a crime wave threatens to tear them apart.
name: The Investigation

description: The young Skylanders learn that Pop Fizz used to be in a rock band with Wolfgang, who plans to turn fans at a music festival into an army of drones.
name: Pop Rocks
